[According to Malawi's annual OIE report, a total of 35 ASF outbreaks
were recorded during 2010 in the following provinces: Kasungu,
Lilongwe, Nkhotakota, Salima, Chitipa, Karonga, Mzimba, Blantyre,
Chikwawa and Nsanje. Map at:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/africa/malawi_pol85.jpg. - Mod.AS]
